TIME SERIES FORECASTING - SPARKLING WINE DATASET¶

Problem Statement:¶

For this particular assignment, the data of different types of wine sales in the 20th century is to be analysed. Both of these data are from the same company but of different wines. As an analyst in the ABC Estate Wines, you are tasked to analyse and forecast Wine Sales in the 20th century.

--

We have given 2 datasets. Let's look at the first dataset, i.e., Sparkling.csv

Simple Exponential Smoothing model¶

Simple Exponential Smoothing, is a time series forecasting method for univariate data without a trend or seasonality. It requires a single parameter, called alpha (a), also called the smoothing factor or smoothing coefficient.

This method is suitable for forecasting data with no clear trend or seasonal pattern.

SES is represented as: Ft+1=Yt+(1)Ft

Parameter is called the smoothing constant and its value lies between 0 and 1. Since the model uses only one smoothing constant, it is called Single Exponential Smoothing.

In [57]:
#importing ExponentialSmoothing, SimpleExpSmoothing and Holt

from statsmodels.tsa.api import ExponentialSmoothing, SimpleExpSmoothing, Holt
In [58]:

SimpleExpSmoothing class must be instantiated and passed the training data.

The fit() function is then called providing the fit configuration, the alpha value, smoothing_level. If this is omitted or set to None, the model will automatically optimize the value.

5. Check for the stationarity of the data on which the model is being built on using appropriate statistical tests and also mention the hypothesis for the statistical test. If the data is found to be non-stationary, take appropriate steps to make it stationary. Check the new data for stationarity and comment. Note: Stationarity should be checked at alpha = 0.05.¶

To check the stationarity of the data, first we need to perform Dickey Fuller test¶

Dickey Fuller Test:

For this test, we need to make null and alternate hypothesis:

We will take the Null Hypothesis $H_0$ as - Series is not Stationary.

and Alternative Hypothesis $H_1$ as - Series is Stationary.

Since We have to proof that data is stationary and also we will take steps to make the data stationary.

In [76]:
#creating a function to test the stationarity of the time series


def Stationarity_test(timeseries):
    
    #rolling mean
    rolmean = timeseries.rolling(window=7).mean() 
    #rolling standard deviation
    rolstd = timeseries.rolling(window=7).std()   

    #Plotting
    
    original = plt.plot(timeseries, color='green',label='Original')
    mean = plt.plot(rolmean, color='orange', label='Rolling mean')
    std = plt.plot(rolstd, color='red', label = 'Rolling std')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('Rolling Mean & Standard Deviation')
    plt.show(block=False)

10.Comment on the model thus built and report your findings and suggest the measures that the company should be taking for future sales.¶

Some Measures that company need to take care of in future:¶

We have observed the highest Sales happened in the year 1987, and the lowest sales observed in the year 1995. From the decomposition plot, we saw that the trend and seasonality are present in the dataset. We have analyzed from boxplot (monthly plot) that sales has been increased from month of September to month of December. We have built various models and tested on test data and also calculated RMSE values on test data to predict the forecast for next 12 months or more. We have also observed that the original dataset has some seasonality pattern. Found out that SARIMA has the lowest RMSE value. So the same model later was applied on full data. On the basis of final and most optimum model, the sales for next 12 month is predicted with confidence interval. Company should keep its focus on reserved stock during the peak time, and in January, the sales recorded the lowest. This is due to the fact that the December month usually observe more number of sales because of the year end and festive season phase. For the positive side, company should maintain its production on the basis of median values which is around to 2000. By doing so, company can fulfill the demands of the customers during the peak time and that also without any additional cost and any extra workers in the factory. If we are able to take these above steps carefully then definitely our sales of the Sparkling wine will improve in upcoming future.
